---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 2
title: Industries
description: Sovereign AI use cases for Switzerland's regulated sectors — banking & finance, healthcare & pharma, legal, government, insurance and manufacturing. Custom models fine-tuned on Apertus, deployed on-prem with zero data egress.
faq:
  - q: Which industries do you serve?
    a: We focus on regulated and data-sensitive sectors in Switzerland and the EU — banking and finance, healthcare and pharma, legal and professional services, government and the public sector, insurance, and manufacturing.
  - q: Can you work with our existing systems?
    a: Yes. Agents call into your existing systems and data sources through tools and retrieval, so the AI works with your core banking, KIS/EHR, DMS, ERP, claims or case-management systems rather than replacing them.
  - q: We operate across languages — is that supported?
    a: Apertus is multilingual by construction — native German, French, Italian and Romansh, including Swiss German, plus 1,000+ further languages.
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, cta, icon, iconChip %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">Industries</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Built for the sectors that can't send data away.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Art. 47 banking secrecy, patient data under Art. 9 GDPR, legal privilege, cantonal data-protection law — the blocker differs by sector; the answer is the same: a model fine-tuned on your documents, running inside your walls.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="container-x divide-y divide-ink-900/10 dark:divide-white/10">
  {% set industries = [
    {
